1. The study lasted for 12 weeks.
2. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in decrease of neck pain intensity on VAS.
3. The decrease of neck pain intensity on VAS was -7.0 mm.
4. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease of neck pain intensity on VAS was between -20.7 to +6.7.
5. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in the mean number of neck pain days.
6. The mean number of neck pain days decreased by -1%.
7. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in mean number of neck pain days was between -15% to +13%.
8. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in neck pain hours per day.
9. The neck pain hours per day decreased by -0.14.
10. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in neck pain hours per day was between -3.0 to +2.7.
11. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in days on which symptomatic treatment was taken.
12. The days on which symptomatic treatment was taken decreased by -0.7%.
13. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in days on which symptomatic treatment was taken was between -15% to +13%.
14. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in the number of analgesics taken per day.
15. The number of analgesics taken per day decreased by -0.14.
16. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in number of analgesics taken per day was between -0.6 to +0.4.
17. There was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in total cervical range of motion.
18. The total cervical range of motion decreased by -11 degrees.
19. The 95% confidence interval for the decrease in total cervical range of motion was between -40 to +17.

Statement: After 12 weeks there was no significant difference between the two treatment groups in decrease of neck pain intensity on VAS (−7.0 mm, 95% confidence interval (CI) [−20.7 to +6.7]), mean number of neck pain days (−1%; 95% CI [−15% to +13%]), neck pain hours per day (−0.14; 95% CI [−3.0 to +2.7]), days on which symptomatic treatment was taken (−0.7%; 95% CI [−15% to +13%]) number of analgesics taken per day (−0.14; 95% CI [−0.6 to +0.4]) and total cervical range of motion (−11 degrees; 95% CI [−40 to +17]).
